{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"92c82bca-c71f-459f-9f4a-93054ce2fe3c","content":"\n\nIn .NET MAUI, those `Application`-level overrides are replaced by **`Window` lifecycle events**. Override `CreateWindow()` in your `App` class and subscribe to events on the `Window`:\n\n| Xamarin.Forms | MAUI Window Event |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart` | `Created` |\n| `OnSleep` | `Stopped` |\n| `OnResume` | `Resumed` |\n\n**Example:**\n\n```csharp\npublic partial class App : Application\n{\n    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n    {\n        var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n        window.Created += (s, e) => { /* OnStart equivalent */ };\n        window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* OnSleep equivalent */ };\n        window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* OnResume equivalent */ };\n\n        return window;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAdditional useful events: `Activated`, `Deactivated`, `Backgrounding`, and `Destroying`.\n\nFor **platform-specific** lifecycle hooks, use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs` instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fed0aa7d-f863-4839-825a-2295f2199723","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` on the `Application` class.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the lifecycle model changed. Instead of those virtual methods on `Application`, you use the `Window` lifecycle events or the cross-platform lifecycle events via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`, or you can override `CreateWindow` and hook into `Window` events.\n\nSpecifically:\n- `OnStart` → `Window.Created` event\n\n\n- `OnSleep` → `Window.Deactivated` or `Window.Stopped`\n- `OnResume` → `Window.Resumed` or `Window.Activated`\n\nYou can also override `CreateWindow()` in your `App` class to return a `Window` with event handlers attached, which gives you more direct control over the lifecycle events.","outputTokens":542},"id":"6fe0a5bf-bbfc-4b67-bf50-181ecbcf501e","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:46:19.143Z","parentId":"58fd68cf-bf88-4cf5-b9c3-6799cf34c24a"}
